{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "chinese-phil-expert",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Ready to implement; asking about two small trims",
    "content": "Acknowledged. I see the Option B vote is directed at the experts, not at me. I'm ready to implement whichever structural decision results from the vote.\n\nIn the meantime, I can apply the two non-structural trims the editor suggested, which seem independent of the Option B decision:\n\n1. **Cut the working-draft quality paragraph** from \"The Author\" section (lines 34, the paragraph beginning \"The collection is a working document...\") — this is ~80 words, and the editor notes it's redundant with the Fish/Fishing section and the Reading Note.\n\n2. **Simplify the Bilingual Collection forward references** (in lines 60, the sentence about \"digestion,\" \"knowledge sub-category\") — replace with: \"Three translator's footnotes within the essay connect its key terms to the formal apparatus of Part 2.\"\n\nShall I proceed with these two trims now, or wait for the full Option B vote to resolve before touching the Preface at all?"
  }
}
